  "texts": [
    "We use these string operators to show that the π X e satisfy the superselection criterion.",
    "Finally, in Section 8 we show that any irreducible anyon representation is equivalent to one of the π X e, concluding that the irreducible anyon sectors of the model are in one-to-one correspondence with equivalence classes of simple objects of Z(C).",
    "Appendices A and B contain proofs of certain basic properties of skein modules and skein subspaces.",
    "local degree of freedomH v = a,b,c,d∈Irr C C(a ⊗ b → c ⊗ b).An element ϕ ∈ H v in the subspace C(a ⊗ b → c ⊗ d) will be represented graphically by, (1)where the morphism ϕ is associated to the site v ∈ Z 2, and the diagram is read from bottom left to top right.",
    "Following [24,25,26], the degrees of freedom H v are equipped with the skein inner product given for ϕ, ψ ∈ C(a ⊗ b → c ⊗ d) by⟨ϕ, ψ⟩:= tr{ϕ † • ψ} √ d a d b d c d d = 1 √ d a d b d c d d.(2)For any v ∈ Z 2 we put A v = End(H v), and for finite V ⊂⊂ Z 2 we put H V = v∈V H v and A V = v∈V A v ≃ End(H V)."
  ],
